cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.GR 

The paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to analyze satellite imagery data for predicting food security outcomes. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of transfer learning and Bayesian networks also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the proposed tasking algorithms involve search algorithms, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
